					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Oh, the method tokumaru posted looks quite organized and powerful. Personally I just don't work with &quot;states&quot; at all. To pause the game, well I just read the controller until start is pressed again and then return. Same for the title screen, I have a loop and when start is pressed, it continues down into the main program. It is just logical for me. However, it might not be as organized.<br /><br />I think what I describe above could be considered multiple game loops. However, all of them are implicit, they are just natural, because I don't leave a routine (or part of a routine) until some event happen that makes me leave it with the rts instruction.</div>

