				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">When using NESASM, remember these feature of its syntax:<ul><li>For zero page addressing, put &lt; before the address or label (for example <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">LDA &lt;var0</tt> if your variable in the zero page is called var0).</li><li>For indirection in all cases, you must use square brackets rather than parentheses.</li></ul>Some people (including myself) prefer this nonstandard syntax, although still remember it is nonstandard and many documents don't use it.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="gopher://zzo38computer.org/" class="postlink">.</a></div>
